      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must use a geometry, flow regime, and fluid properties sufficiently similar to the COU device and operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which shares the same impeller topology and CPB operating range as the subject device. Blood analog fluid properties were matched. The validation domain is judged sufficiently representative of the COU for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Numerical solver error beyond discretization (e.g., iterative convergence, round-off) need not be formally quantified at MRL 2 if residuals are monitored.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 the required level for this factor is 1 (not-assessed is acceptable). Residual convergence to 1e-6 was monitored and confirmed for all simulations; no formal solver error quantification beyond this monitoring is required."
    },
    {
