      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal use error analysis is not required at MRL 2 provided simulation setup is performed by qualified analysts under documented procedures.",
      "rationale": "Simulations were executed by engineers with documented CFD training records. Setup checklists and peer review of boundary condition inputs were completed. Formal use error quantification is scoped out at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form uncertainty (turbulence model selection, hemolysis damage model) need not be formally quantified at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model were selected based on published literature recommendations for rotary blood pump CFD. Formal model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs including blood viscosity, density, and hemolysis model coefficients must be documented with sources and uncertainty ranges.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog fluid properties (viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s, density 1056 kg/m³) are documented with literature sources. Hemolysis model coefficients (C=3.62e-5, alpha=2.416, beta=0.785) are taken from Giersiepen et al. and confirmed against the 2018 experimental calibration dataset. Input uncertainty ranges are tabulated in the simulation report. Note: the experimental calibration dataset carries a dataVintage of 2018-03-22, predating the current model revision of 2026-01-15; the hemolysis coefficient values have not been re-evaluated against any post-2018 experimental data."
    },
